Key Match Events: Yordan Alvarez homered and Kyle Tucker added two RBIs to give him an American League-leading 101.
Jurickson Profar had three hits, highlighted by a two-run homer.
Ryan Pressly struck out Manny Machado and Xander Bogaerts to end the threat and get his 30th save.
Phil Maton pitched a perfect fifth for the win.
San Diego hit three straight singles with one out in the sixth to add a run and cut the lead to 7-5.
